      <hedline>
        <hl1>N.T.T. RETREATS ON CONNECTION FEES</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Stephanie Strom</byline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Shares of the Nippon Telegraph and Telephone Corporation, Japan's former telephone monopoly, climbed 6.4 percent after the company indicated it would bow to pressure to lower fees it charges other carriers to hook into its local network at a faster pace. N.T.T. also sharply increased its earnings forecasts to 172 billion yen from 99 billion yen because of growing dial-up Internet use by consumers.</p>
        <p>Stephanie Strom (NYT)</p>
      </block>
